      <section eId="sec_207">
        <num>207</num>
        <heading>Defendant's absence from state or residence under false name</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_207__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_207__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of section three hundred six-b of this chapter\nshall be computed in accordance with this section. This section does not\napply:\n  1. while there is in force a designation, voluntary or involuntary,\nmade pursuant to law, of a person to whom a summons may be delivered\nwithin the state with the same effect as if served personally within the\nstate; or\n  2. while a foreign corporation has one or more officers or other\npersons in the state on whom a summons against such corporation may be\nserved; or\n  3. while jurisdiction over the person of the defendant can be obtained\nwithout personal delivery of the summons to the defendant within the\nstate.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
